instruction: Explain a book in less than 3 sentences.
input: The Catcher in the Rye by J.D. Salinger
output: The Catcher in the Rye is a 1951 novel by J.D. Salinger. It follows protagonist Holden Caulfield as he struggles with feelings of alienation and loss of innocence. The novel has become a classic of post-World War II literature and has been cited as an influence on subsequent generations of writers.
